        <updateDate>2005-06-14T15:28:49Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Asbestos Standards Enforcement Act of 2005 - Amends the Occupational Safety and Health Act of 1970 to subject any employer convicted of willfully violating a standard issued with respect to the control of occupational exposure to asbestos to a fine and/or up to five years' imprisonment for a first offense or a fine and/or up to 10 years' imprisonment for subsequent convictions.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
